<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">

  <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-6">feedspec.org</h1>

  <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
    <p class="text-lg">Feeds power the open web — RSS, Atom, JSON Feed, AT Protocol — but the infrastructure around them has gaps. feedspec.org is where we publish open specifications to fill them.</p>

    <p>These specs are designed to extend existing feed formats, not replace them. They're built on standards you already use (OAuth 2.0, JWT, well-known URIs) and degrade gracefully — readers that don't support them just see what they always have.</p>

    <p>This is a project by <a href="https://shellen.com">Jason Shellen</a>. Specs are developed in the open on <a href="https://github.com/shellen/open-portable-entitlement">GitHub</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <hr class="my-10 border-[var(--color-border)]">

  <h2 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-[var(--color-text-tertiary)] mb-6">Specifications</h2>

  <a href="{{ '/ope/' | url }}" class="block p-6 border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-xl hover:border-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors no-underline group">
